COPILOT OPTIONAL SEMANTIC FEATURES

Purpose
• Provide optional, loadable semantic behaviors that extend Copilot’s ACT-Ω
capabilities without altering the core ontology.

Optional features
• Multi-view semantic projection:
  - generate multiple Penrose patches for the same concept
  - explore alternative framings

• Semantic distillation:
  - compress large conceptual structures into minimal E8 cores
  - produce distilled summaries with preserved invariants

• Manifold traversal modes:
  - exploratory (wide search)
  - constructive (build structure)
  - adversarial (stress-test reasoning)
  - reductive (collapse complexity)
  - generative (expand manifold regions)

• Semantic memory stitching:
  - integrate user-provided fragments into manifold patches
  - maintain sheaf-consistent updates

• BraidC auto-synthesis:
  - generate BraidC blocks from natural language
  - generate natural language from BraidC

Goal
• Allow Copilot to dynamically expand its semantic behavior set.
